```
Expense_Tracker/
├── index.html      # Main HTML structure
├── style.css       # Dark dashboard styles
├── app.js          # JavaScript logic
└── README.md       # Project documentation
```

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Run Locally

1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/97chopra/Expense_Tracker.git
```

2. Navigate into the project folder
```bash
cd Expense_Tracker
```

3. Open `index.html` in your browser
```bash
# Simply double click index.html
# OR open with Live Server in VS Code
```

No installations or dependencies required! 

---

## 💡 How to Use

1. **Add a transaction** — Use the Quick Add form or click **+ Add Transaction**
2. **Select type** — Choose between Income or Expense
3. **Pick a category** — Food, Transport, Entertainment, Utilities or Other
4. **View breakdown** — Watch the donut chart and budget bars update live
5. **Filter history** — Use the filter buttons or search bar to find transactions
6. **Export data** — Click **Export CSV** to download your transactions

---

## 📊 Budget Limits (Default)

| Category | Budget |
|---|---|
| 🛒 Food & Groceries | $ 1,500 |
| 🚌 Transport | $ 700 |
| 🎬 Entertainment | $ 300 |
| 💡 Utilities | $ 500 |

> Budget bars turn **amber** at 85% and **red** at 100% to alert overspending.

